{
  "texts": [
    "ducation has changed to a dynamic focus on skill development under Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) instead of a traditional emphasis on knowledge acquisition (Aslam et al. 2023; Kopnina, 2020; Nazar et al. 2018).",
    "Moreover, science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) education has undergone a significant paradigm shift, especially in STEM fields (Felder, 2021; Koutsopoulos, 2019; Nadelson and Seifert, 2017; Rehman et al. 2023).",
    "In the U.S., STEM disciplines are increasingly integrated to shape a future-ready workforce (Zhan and Niu, 2023; Hoeg and Bencze, 2017; Li et al. 2020).",
    "A similar trend occurs in China, where STEM education is integrated into its academic renaissance (Zhong et al. 2022; Ma, 2021; Loyalka et al. 2021).",
    "However, unlike in the U.S., China's approach to integrating STEM into its educational system is uniquely shaped by its socio-economic goals and cultural context."
  ]
}